Condition : 5 - Prior to the commencement of the development, a Construction Management Plan (CMP) shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The CMP shall include: 
i. confirmation that a pre-start record of site conditions on the adjoining public highway will be undertaken with Hounslow Highways and a commitment to repair any damage caused;
ii. appropriate vehicle routes to and from the site;
ii. details of access to the site for the duration of construction;
iii. means to control and manage access and egress of vehicles to and from the site including vehicle turning and waiting areas;
iv. provisions for loading, unloading and storage of plant and materials within the site;
v. measures to prevent the spread of mud, dust, loose materials etc. onto the public highway (such as the provision of wheel washing facilities at the site exit and a commitment to sweep adjacent roads);
vi. details of delivery hours to avoid peak times;
vii. provision for the parking of vehicles of site operatives and visitors;
viii. measures to control the emission of dust and dirt during construction, with particular reference to adjoining properties; 
ix. a scheme for recycling/disposing of waste resulting from demolition and construction works;
x. the erection and maintenance of security hoarding;
xi. measures to ensure the safety of all users of the public highway in the vicinity of the site, especially at the access, with particular reference to cyclists and pedestrians;
xii. details of any external illumination on site;
xiii. contractor membership of the Fleet Operator Recognition Scheme (FORS) or similar.
The approved CMP shall be adhered to throughout the construction period.
